handist.collections.dist

Class DistLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • handist.collections.dist.DistCollectionSatellite<DistConcurrentMultiMap<DistLog.LogKey,DistLog.LogItem>,DistLog>
      • handist.collections.dist.DistLog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    apgas.util.SerializableWithReplace, Serializable

    public class DistLog
extends DistCollectionSatellite<DistConcurrentMultiMap<DistLog.LogKey,DistLog.LogItem>,DistLog>
implements Serializable
    DistLog is a distributed log manager. It collects log on places and gather it to a place. Each DistLog instance refers to a distributed collection having global ID and you can arbitrary copy it to other places. It offers a static method DistLog.log(tag, msg). Please call `DistLog.globalSetup(DistLog)` first, otherwise the method only print the tag and msg to System.out.

        Parameters:
        tag - the topic tag about which a log is made
        msg - object being logged, can be a String or another object
        appendix - appendix of the log message

      • distributionFreeEquals

        public boolean distributionFreeEquals(DistLog target,
                                      PrintStream out)
        Determines whether the log set of this and the target DistLog instances are equal. It distinguish only tags and ignores the generated places. It return true iff the sets of the logs having the same tag are the same. Diff will be output to out if they differ.
        Parameters:
        target - the logger instance to compare to this
        out - the output to which the difference is printed
        Returns:
        true if this instance and the target are identical, false otherwise

      • getLog

        public Collection<DistLog.LogItem> getLog(apgas.Place p,
                                          String key)
        Returns the logged items of the specified place for the specified key and the current phase. If the specified place is the local place, then calling this method is equivalent to calling method getLog(String). If the specified place is remote, then programmers should be careful to call method globalGather() so that events logged on remote hosts are relocated and accessible on this host.
        Parameters:
        p - the place on which the logged events occurred
        key - the key under which the events were recorded
        Returns:
        the collection of items logged under the specified key at the specified host

      • getLog

        public Collection<DistLog.LogItem> getLog(apgas.Place p,
                                          String tag,
                                          long phase)
        Returns the logged items of the specified place, tag and phase.

        Note that is the targeted log entries are of a remote host, method globalGather() should be called prior to attempting to retrieve such logs.

        Parameters:
        p - the place on which events were recorded
        tag - the tag under which events were recorded
        phase - the phase during which the events were recorded
        Returns:
        the collection of DistLog.LogItem recorded under the specified key
